{"id":"quant-ph/0204173","submitter":"Martin Ligare","authors":"Thomas Purdy and Martin Ligare","title":"Electromagnetically induced transparency and reduced speeds for single\n  photons in a fully quantized model","comments":"14 pages, 7 figures, REVTeX4, submitted to Phys. Rev. A","journal-ref":"J. Opt B: Quantum Semiclass. Opt., vol. 5, 289-299 (2003)","doi":"10.1088/1464-4266/5/3/315","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph physics.optics","license":null,"abstract":"  We introduce a simple model for electromagnetically induced transparency in\nwhich all fields are treated quantum mechanically. We study a system of three\nseparated atoms at fixed positions in a one-dimensional multimode optical\ncavity. The first atom serves as the source for a single spontaneously emitted\nphoton; the photon scatters from a three-level Lambda-configuration atom which\ninteracts with a single-mode field coupling two of the atomic levels; the third\natom serves as a detector of the total transmitted field. We find an analytical\nsolution for the quantum dynamics. From the quantum amplitude describing the\nexcitation of the detector atom we extract information that provides exact\nsingle-photon analogs to wave delays predicted by semi-classical theories. We\nalso find complementary information in the expectation value of the electric\nfield intensity operator.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Apr 2002 17:36:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-09"}
