{"id":"quant-ph/0205004","submitter":"Xiao Gang Wen","authors":"Xiao-Gang Wen","title":"Quantum orders in an exact soluble model","comments":"4 pages, RevTeX4, More materials on topological/quantum orders and\n  quantum computing can be found in http://dao.mit.edu/~wen","journal-ref":"Phys.Rev.Lett.90:016803,2003","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevLett.90.016803","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph cond-mat.str-el hep-th","license":null,"abstract":"  We find all the exact eigenstates and eigenvalues of a spin-1/2 model on\nsquare lattice: $H=16g \\sum_i S^y_i S^x_{i+x} S^y_{i+x+y} S^x_{i+y}$. We show\nthat the ground states for $g<0$ and $g>0$ have different quantum orders\ndescribed by Z2A and Z2B projective symmetry groups. The phase transition at\n$g=0$ represents a new kind of phase transitions that changes quantum orders\nbut not symmetry. Both the Z2A and Z2B states are described by $Z_2$ lattice\ngauge theories at low energies. They have robust topologically degenerate\nground states and gapless edge excitations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 May 2002 15:49:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 8 May 2002 03:39:08 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 29 Aug 2002 13:59:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-07-19"}
